Dear Hiring Manager,
I am writing to express my strong interest in the Data Scientist position. With a PhD in Public Health Sciences, over eight years of experience applying advanced analytics to complex business and research problems, and a current role leading a team of data scientists and analysts at Presage Group, I am confident I can drive meaningful impact on your product growth, monetization, and experimentation efforts.
As Director of Analytics at Presage Group, I lead a team that solves complex analytical problems for clients in the airline industry—work that demands a deep understanding of customer behavior, engagement metrics, and business operations at scale. I collaborate directly with executive leadership to implement data governance best practices and translate analytical findings into strategic decisions. This experience has sharpened my ability to work cross-functionally, communicate insights to diverse stakeholders, and prioritize ruthlessly in fast-moving environments.
My technical background aligns closely with your requirements. I am proficient in Python, R, and SQL, with deep expertise in statistical modeling, experiment design, and predictive analytics. My career has centered on building prediction models—from forecasting cancer outcomes at Sunnybrook Health Sciences Centre to developing dental readiness models for the Canadian Armed Forces—and I bring that same rigor to segmentation, propensity modeling, and multivariate testing. I have extensive experience with automated reporting and dashboard development, and I am comfortable working with large, complex, multi-dimensional datasets to extract actionable insights.
Beyond technical skills, I bring strong communication abilities honed through seven semesters of teaching graduate-level statistics and quantitative analysis at Queen’s University, as well as a record of peer-reviewed publications in leading journals. I understand how to translate complex analytical concepts into clear, actionable implications for business audiences—whether that means presenting to senior executives or partnering with product and engineering teams to shape experimentation roadmaps.
I am excited about the opportunity to apply my experience in predictive modeling, customer behavior analysis, and data-driven decision-making to help grow and optimize your product. I would welcome the chance to discuss how my background and skills can contribute to your team’s goals.
Sincerely,
Randall Boyes, PhD

